            <li><strong>Adopt a Comfortable Posture:</strong> Sit upright on a chair or a cushion. Keep your spine straight but relaxed, letting your hands rest gently on your knees.</li>
            <li><strong>Close Your Eyes:</strong> Soften your gaze or close your eyes completely to reduce external visual stimulation.</li>
            <li><strong>Locate Your Breath Anchor:</strong> Focus on where you feel the breath most clearly—whether it is the rising of your belly, the expansion of your ribs, or the cool sensation at your nostrils.</li>
            <li><strong>Observe Wandering Thoughts:</strong> When thoughts arise (as they will), acknowledge them like passing clouds in the sky, and gently return your attention back to the breath.</li>
          </ul>

